				                <div>Hello Alex, <br />
<br />
The .htaccess is a <i>hidden</i> file.  If you're using the cPanel File Manager and you have not set it to view hidden files, then you will not see the .htaccess file.  You can reset the File Manager settings by logging into cPanel and then going to the bottom of the screen and selecting "reset all interface settings".    Then when you go into the file manager, make sure to click on "Show Hidden Files".   This will let you see the .htaccess file.  If you created an .htaccess file previously, remember that case (no capital letters) and the period at the front of the file name are required for this file to operate correctly.<br />
<br />
